history.content: 61b and some linear algebra are the only real requirements, but they do use C++, so knowing C from 61c does help. The workload is decent, but it isn't 162 level at least. You've taken 170, so that should help, not in the sense that they use 170 algorithms, but you would be more comfortable with the types of algorithms used. With 161, it shouldn't be bad unless project deadlines overlap, but you would know if they will from the beginning of the semester and can plan accordingly

Hi,

I’m trying to plan my schedule and the only CS class I really have set in stone is 161. I really want to take 184 alongside it but I’m worried that the workload will be insane and that I don’t have the necessarily background to do well in it. For context, the theory classes I have taken so far are 70, 170 and 16A. What do you guys think is needed to do well in 184?
